      <description>Shohei Katakura(片倉翔平) is a Master’s student at Graduate School of Advanced Mathematical Sciences, Meiji University, advised by Prof. Keita Watanabe.
His research fields are mainly human-computer interaction (HCI) and personal fabrication. In particular, he is interested in repurposing things that we already have or use in daily life in order to create functional objects and physical experience.
